efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1)
space complexity: O(n)
explanation: Uses two stacks. The main stack stores all elements, and the min_stack stores the minimum element encountered so far. When pushing, if the new element is less than or equal to the current minimum, it's added to the min_stack. Popping removes from the main stack, and if the popped element is the current minimum, it's also removed from the min_stack.  This allows for constant time complexity for all operations.

